study_id: unique ID for each study - numeric/character
author: first author name - numeric/character
all_info_expected: expected input data leading to an effect size estimate - character
n_exp: number of participants in the exposed/experimental group - numeric
n_nexp: number of participants in the non-exposed/non-experimental group - numeric
reverse_means: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the means should be flipped - logical
mean_exp: mean of participants in the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_sd_exp: standard deviation of participants in the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_se_exp: standard error of participants in the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_ci_lo_exp: lower bound of the 95% CI of the mean of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_ci_up_exp: upper bound of the 95% CI of the mean of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_nexp: mean of participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
mean_sd_nexp: standard deviation of participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
mean_se_nexp: standard error of participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
mean_ci_lo_nexp: lower bound of the 95% CI of the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
mean_ci_up_nexp: upper bound of the 95% CI of the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
mean_sd_pooled: pooled standard deviation across both groups - numeric
reverse_plot_means: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the means extracted from a plot should be flipped - logical
plot_mean_exp: mean of participants in the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_nexp: mean of participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_sd_lo_exp: lower bound of an error bar depicting -1 SD from the mean of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_sd_lo_nexp: lower bound of an error bar depicting -1 SD from the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_sd_up_exp: upper bound of an error bar depicting +1 SD from the mean of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_sd_up_nexp: upper bound of an error bar depicting +1 SD from the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_se_lo_exp: lower bound of an error bar depicting -1 SE from the mean of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_se_lo_nexp: lower bound of an error bar depicting -1 SE from the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_se_up_exp: upper bound of an error bar depicting +1 SE from the mean of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_se_up_nexp: upper bound of an error bar depicting +1 SE from the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_ci_lo_exp: lower bound of an error bar depicting the 95% CI of the mean of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_ci_lo_nexp: lower bound of an error bar depicting the 95% CI of the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_ci_up_exp: upper bound of an error bar depicting the 95% CI of the mean of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_mean_ci_up_nexp: upper bound of an error bar depicting the 95% CI of the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
reverse_means_variability: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the means variability should be flipped - logical
reverse_md: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the mean difference should be flipped - logical
md_sd: standard deviation of the mean difference - numeric
md_se: standard error of the mean difference - numeric
md_ci_lo: lower bound of the 95% CI of the mean difference - numeric
md_ci_up: upper bound of the 95% CI of the mean difference - numeric
md_pval: p-value of the mean difference - numeric
reverse_d: whether the direction of the cohen_d value should be flipped - logical
cohen_d: value of the Cohen's d - numeric
reverse_g: whether the direction of the hedges_g value should be flipped - logical
hedges_g: value of the Hedges' g - numeric
reverse_student_t: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the Student's t-test should be flipped - logical
reverse_student_t_pval: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the Student's t-test p-value should be flipped - logical
student_t_pval: two-tailed p-value of a Student's t-test - numeric
reverse_anova_f: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the ANOVA F should be flipped - logical
reverse_anova_f_pval: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the ANOVA p-value should be flipped - logical
anova_f_pval: two-tailed p-value of an ANOVA - numeric
reverse_etasq: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the eta-squared should be flipped - logical
reverse_pt_bis_r: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the point-biserial correlation should be flipped - logical

pt_bis_r_pval: p-value of a point-biserial correlation - numeric
reverse_beta_std: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the standardized beta should be flipped - logical
beta_std: a standardized regression coefficient value (the predictor of interest must be binary) - numeric
reverse_beta_unstd: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the unstandardized beta should be flipped - logical
beta_unstd: a non-standardized regression coefficient value (the predictor of interest must be binary) - numeric
sd_dv: standard deviation of the dependent variable (not the standard deviation of the regression coefficient) - numeric
reverse_means_pre_post: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the pre/post means should be flipped - logical

mean_pre_sd_exp: standard deviation of the experimental/exposed group at baseline - numeric
mean_pre_se_exp: standard error of the experimental/exposed group at baseline - numeric

mean_pre_ci_up_exp: mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group at baseline - numeric
mean_pre_nexp: standard deviation of the non-experimental/non-exposed group at baseline - numeric
mean_pre_sd_nexp: standard error of the non-experimental/non-exposed group at baseline - numeric
mean_pre_ci_lo_nexp: lower bound of the 95% CI of the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group at baseline - numeric
mean_pre_ci_up_nexp: upper bound of the 95% CI of the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group at baseline - numeric
reverse_mean_change: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the mean change should be flipped - logical
mean_change_exp: mean change of participants in the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_change_nexp: mean change of participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
mean_change_sd_exp: standard deviation of the mean change for participants in the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_change_sd_nexp: standard deviation of the mean change for participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
mean_change_se_exp: standard error of the mean change for participants in the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_change_se_nexp: standard error of the mean change for participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric

mean_change_ci_up_exp: upper bound of the 95% CI of the mean change for the experimental/exposed group - numeric
mean_change_ci_lo_nexp: lower bound of the 95% CI of the mean change for the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric

r_pre_post_exp: pre-post correlation in the experimental/exposed group - numeric
r_pre_post_nexp: pre-post correlation in the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
reverse_med: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the medians/quartiles/ranges should be flipped - logical
min_exp: minimum value of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
q1_exp: first quartile of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
med_exp: median value of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
q3_exp: third quartile of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
max_exp: maximum value of the experimental/exposed group - numeric

q1_nexp: first quartile of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
med_nexp: median value of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
q3_nexp: third quartile of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
max_nexp: maximum value of the non-experimental/non-exposed  group - numeric
reverse_paired_t: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the paired t-tests should be flipped - logical
paired_t_exp: paired t-test value of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
paired_t_nexp: paired t-test value of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric

paired_t_pval_exp: p-value of the paired t-test value of the experimental/exposed group - numeric

reverse_paired_f: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the paired F-tests should be flipped - logical

paired_f_nexp: paired ANOVA F value of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric

paired_f_pval_exp: p-value of the paired ANOVA-F of the experimental/exposed group - numeric
paired_f_pval_nexp: p-value of the paired ANOVA-F of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric
reverse_ancova_means: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the ANCOVA means should be flipped - logical
cov_outcome_r: correlation between the outcome and covariate(s) (multiple correlation when multiple covariates are included in the ANCOVA model) - numeric
n_cov_ancova: number of covariates in the ANCOVA model - numeric

ancova_mean_nexp: adjusted standard deviation of participants in the experimental/exposed group - numeric

ancova_mean_se_exp: upper bound of the adjusted 95% CI of the mean of the experimental/exposed group - numeric

ancova_mean_ci_up_nexp: upper bound of the adjusted 95% CI of the mean of the non-experimental/non-exposed group - numeric

plot_ancova_mean_ci_lo_exp: lower bound of an error bar depicting the 95% CI of the adjusted mean (from ANCOVA) of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_ancova_mean_ci_up_exp: upper bound of an error bar depicting the 95% CI of the adjusted mean (from ANCOVA) of the experimental/exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric
plot_ancova_mean_nexp: adjusted mean (from ANCOVA) of participants in the non-experimental/non-exposed group (extracted from a plot) - numeric

reverse_ancova_t: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the ANCOVA t-test should be flipped - logical
ancova_t: a t-statistic from an ANCOVA - numeric
reverse_ancova_f: whether the direction of the effect size generated from the ANCOVA F-test should be flipped - logical
ancova_f: a F-statistic from an ANCOVA - numeric
